<h2><a name="setbuf" id="setbuf">setbuf</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">void</span> setbuf<span class="br0">&#40;</span> FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>stream<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>buffer <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

The setbuf() function sets stream to use buffer, or, if buffer is null, turns
off buffering. If a non-standard buffer size is used, it should be BUFSIZ
characters long.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="fclose" class="wikilink1" title="c:io:fclose">fclose</a>, <a href="fopen" class="wikilink1" title="c:io:fopen">fopen</a>, <a href="setvbuf" class="wikilink1" title="c:io:setvbuf">setvbuf</a>
</p>

</div>
